<footer class="home-disclaimer">
  <p>
    Baque Fácil is an independent student practice tool created by a beginner learning Maracatu.
  </p>
  <p>
    It is meant to help with personal practice by turning simple text patterns into sound. It is
    not an official teaching resource, not a complete archive and not a substitute for learning
    from instructors, mestres, groups and nações that carry the tradition.
  </p>
  <p>
    The patterns here are based on personal class notes and should be treated as draft practice
    material.
  </p>
  <p>
    The code is open source and available <a href="https://github.com/LuizHAssuncao/baque-facil">here</a>. All rhythms are text files located <a href="https://github.com/LuizHAssuncao/baque-facil/tree/main/src/content/rhythms">here</a>.
  </p>
</footer>
